product_description: Bluetooth Speaker with Built-in MP3 Player
Creative MUVO 2C is perfect for life's adventures
product_name: Creative MUVO 2C WW-R N (Black)
\u00e7omments:
Sound stage is fantastic for a speaker of this size. 
After a firmware upgrade, connection on mobile app unlocks bonus features, tapping on the v4.2 Bluetooth capabilities.    The SD card playback functionality is very matured compared to other manufactures such as Xiaomi.    It allows proper folder and tracks selection as well as both mac & pc compatibly.   

At this moment the L & R expandability (With and additional Muvo2 speaker) is only available when we playback using bluetooth source connected to our mobile devices. it will not work with internal SD or Aux inputs. 

It will be a great bonus if it comes with a semi-hard case for radiator driver protection during storage and transportation.  The only room for improvement is for the additional vol level steps, especially at lower vol it is evident that with each press of either the + or - vol the increment is huge, will be good to have additional steps in between.    Other than that we are also not certain of the longevity of rubberise paint used to coat the speaker.    Based on past products using such painting method, they do turn sticky after sometime due to the reaction to our 'sweat' upon contact.    Hope that the rubberised paint method had improved over the years and it will be a pity if this speaker be succumb to the same 'sticky' fate :)

The Sound Quality Is Amazing With the Vocals And The Bass In Perfect Harmony. The Compact Form Factor Of This Mighty Speaker Is Something That Other Companies Should Take Notes From. A Highly Recommended Buy!
Sound is impressive for its size. It might even perform better than thr bigger ones oht there.
Sound great with extra bass easy to bring along..
A quality portable Bluetooth speaker. Value for money.

\u00e7omments:
Tested out the product and the sound quality is overall great. Tried pushing the sound with deep bass music and it was surprising good for the price. You can really feel each beat and it is clear throughout. Not too overpowering and the sound are well-balance between singer's voice and music. It is stereo earpiece hence its a given. Shldnt be a problem for people who use it to exercise in the gym. When running of course you can hear your breathing no matter how expensive the earpice is but it works.

Tried the phone function as well, the caller's voice was loud and clear with little white noises. The microphone feedback was surprisingly good as well. Great for normal conversation with not so loud environment. Just need to be familair with the buttons. After a certain distance around 10metres from the source, the sound gets cracky. So the usable range is arnd there.

The volume +/- button are abit flimpsy and overall it feels plasticky (if there is a word for that). It felt like if too much pressure was given or drop it may just crack but come just be careful with it. The charging port waterproof rubber cover is really well flush on the left earpiece and its abit hard to take it out to charge unless you have long fingernails. The rubber cover is attached to the earpiece hence I feel overtime it may just detached due to frequent usage.

It fits perfectly in your ear and it comes with the standard extra earpiece buds and ear hooks from size s,m to L. Plus it also comes with a nice earpiece bag to keep it in if you dun want it to get dusty. 

I must say I was quite impress overall and with the price I purchased for $36, its worth it for a stereo wireless bluetooth sports earpiece. I tried it on the Samsung S7 phone.
The music sound quality,  comfort level was average. As for phone calling is good, both party get to hear loud n clear and minimum noise
Cant complain for the price - but earphones sounds crackly at times. Fast delivery. ideal for workouts.

Just received upon delivery and charged earbuds as instructed on manual. Manual claims can be fully charged around 2 hours (LED red to blue), mine was red even after charging for 8 hours. Can't even turn on device. Thus, unable to try out audio quality etc. Extremely disappointed as if I just bought a dummy/display version where it doesn't work...
For it's price, the sound is okay and comfortable to wear. However you cannot change song with the ear piece. I think it is because of poor programming.

The only draw back, the box might have been kept in the warehouse for sometimes. All 3 sets of the foam ear tips were sticky, torn as I put them to test.

Overall, I am happy to own this piece at this price!

\u00e7omments:
Great product, easy to use. Small and compact and can go anywhere and once you master how to use it, captures amazing photos and videos.

However, do note that flight time is 16 minutes max, in practise, around 10 - 12 mins depending on how many times you take of and land, wind etc. Strongly recommend the fly-more bundle with extra battery, charger and remote. Actually, 2 extra batteries needed, especially if you are on the road or travelling overseas.

Another point to note is that the drone is so tiny that once it goes beyond a certain distance, its hard to tell which direction its pointing - learn to use the video feed for flying.

I am a Sony AV user who own BRAVIA TV as well as a Sony Soundbar. 
Lately I brought the Sony CT-80 for to pair with another BRAVIA TV setup 
which is my gaming station. 

Good 
- Various connections, Optical, 3.5mm, Bluetooth with NFC. 
For mobile phone users you can use NFC/BT to connect. 
- Various feature to tweak sound for music, movies and games. 
The surround mode as well as Clearaudio+ is not a redundant feature. 
You can play around to get the most out of the Soundbar. 
- Voice type 
If I am correct, Sony Soundbar have various voice type to emphasis on voice. 
However if you emphasis on voice, the vocal will overlap the surround effect. 
- Movie/Gaming performance is good 
- Music performance is also good 

Cons 
- No LED display to indicate volume/settings and etc. 
You have to rely on your ear to make adjustment 

My other Soundbar is the Sony CT-380 so CT-80 is the younger sibling. 
Thus I write from my own experience since I use Sony Soundbar and they don't disappoint. 
One thing I just hope is this product be sold in physical stores other than Lazada. 

If Sony wish to update CT-80 which I think they should especially to cater to various price range. 
Since the other model will cost near $400 so they opt to have some a model that is below that. 
Hopefully the next model, will feature a HDMI ARC input instead. 

A word of advice to all, this model given the power rating of 80 watts as well as it price it is not for all TV sizes. 
If you are using 40"inch and above TV, try to invest in a higher power Soundbar. to compliment the experience. 
Max Lee 
AV Specialist

\u00e7omments: For the record, this is not the real Bobby bag which is selling for S$100+. This is a pretty decent copy, with all the bits in the right places (ie. USB connector facing in rather than exposed), and the layout of the interior follows the original fairly closely. My 15" laptop fits in the primary slot in nicely, although the smaller secondary slot can only hold an iPad mini (not the iPad air). The quality of materials used isn't top-notch, but for S$22.90, I'm not complaining. Beyond the general aesthetics, this Bobby-bag design is brilliant especially since I travel a bit for work. And I can imagine uni students using it as well. I won't recommend this for school children as they generally require more interior space.

product_name: Authentic anello backpack (leather version) Japan hot-selling (large size, Black color)
\u00e7omments: I bought this backpack to use for work and travel. The fake leather finish makes it look more workplace appropriate than the usual canvas version of this backpack. It survived a few work trips as hand baggage loaded with items and fits my laptop comfortably with your daily essentials.  I have had a it for a couple of months and the fake leather is not scratched or scuffed. The bag is roomy, but not so big that you fill it with too many things and it gets to heavy. If I had to pick on one small thing, the bag is hard to zip open with one hand when you are holding the bag with the other hand, but that is easily solved by using the zip at the back to access the contents of the bag. Overall I am very happy with this in terms of quality, durability and look, especially at the sale price of 30 plus dollars.

Fast delivery (It came within the stipulated time given). Good packaging (it came in the original zip lock bag). Authentic (it came with the original tags on the bag). Being leather, the bag is a little bit heavy as compared to normal canvas bags. So if you are looking for a light bag, then this material is probably not for you. Colour is true to the picture above and no defects found. I have purchased two other Anello bags from this same seller and is very satisfied with all my purchases! :)

\u00e7omments: Good mattress, firmness is just the right one for me. Delivery is fast ., and I was not at home - maid received the mattress and the delivery guys knocked so hard on our main door as it if we are deaf! My kid got frightened!

I had bad memories of foam mattresses during the early days of the technology, so I was a little reluctant to get a foam mattress again. However, I saw that the reviews were decent, and that the only hard mattress that I could find was this one.

It really surpassed my expectations. The mattress doesn't trap heat like the ones I had in the past, and it was firmer than any spring mattress I knew!

Since it's a spring mattress, the weight distribution was also much better than my spring mattresess that would end up poking through the aged top material after a few years.

As someone with a weak respiratory system though, I've noticed a marked improvement in my health over the past 3 weeks of sleeping on this mattress. Very glad to have it, but let's see if the anti-allergy claims hold up for the manufacturer.

The other aspects of the foam mattress I can't test are: anti-bacteria, anti-dust mite.

I do hope that Perfecta makes it a point to upload any certifications that they have, since that makes it easier for me to make a decision.

Irritant Contact Dermatitis	A type of skin rash that is triggered by substances that irritate the skin such as chemicals, perfumes, soap or detergents. Symptoms include redness, swelling and itching. This reaction usually worsens the longer the skin is in contact with the offending substance. It can be frequently found on the hands and other exposed parts of the body.
Allergic Contact Dermatitis	A rash commonly caused by fragrances or dyes that the skin is allergic (reacting) to.

Diaper Rash	Most diaper rashes are caused by prolonged exposure to wetness and contact with trapped irritants from human waste products, such as bacteria and enzymes present in faeces and ammonia from stale urine. Another trigger factor is the allergic reaction to lingering detergent or softener found in cloth napkins.

Re: Is New Age Living Pte Ltd from Singapore an official reseller?

Hello,
Thank you for contacting SatoshiLabs customer support. I'm happy to help you.
You don't need to worry, it is our official reseller.
Even if you would purchase TREZOR from not authorized reseller/person, there are several security aspects of each package.
TREZOR box is protected by the seals and it is also virtually impossible to open the device without breaking it ( the case is sealed using ultrasound), so you would see right away if someone tampered with it.
All TREZOR devices are distributed without a firmware software, so you need to install it for your first use. If there is a firmware installed already, then that means that someone used this device before you.
Our Bootloader software, which cannot be replaced or removed, ensures that you're using the valid firmware version signed by us. If not, then there is a warning message on TREZOR display.

Customer Support Supervisor

Waited for 6 days for it to process, only for it to be refunded for NO apparent reason. No email notifications, no explanation why.

A true gaming grade mouse at less than $30 after discount and rebates? Sign me right up and take my money.

The G102 is widely recognized to perform better than most entry level gaming mice from Razer, Steelseries or even Zowie due the prowess of its custom made Mercury sensor, which is comparable to the holy grail PWM3366; Generally regarded as the best sensor available, which is found in its twin: The Logitech G Pro, and many of Logitech's top end line-up. 

Pros:
- Great sensor on par with top tier sensors
- Good quality tactile Omron switches that make satisfying, crisp clicks
- RGB lighting
- On board memory to save mouse settings
- Mouse shape is ideal for most people
- Cheap

Cons:
- May be too small for some people

Forget those "gaming" mice that you see that go for $5, $10 or even $20, as those are not gaming grade mice, unlike this one. At a mere fraction of the Logitech G Pro's retail price, you are getting very close or comparable gaming performance from the G102, which is an absolute bang-for-buck.

So to those out there who are still wondering if they should pull the trigger on this one, here is my two cents: If you are looking for a proper gaming mouse on a budget, look no further.

product_description: 1 x Razer DeathAdder ELITE Gaming Mouse
product_name: Razer DeathAdder Elite Ergonomic Gaming Mouse *IT SHOW PROMO*
\u00e7omments:
Real and Authentic. Basically the feel that fits your hand and your palm is able to rest on the mouse.
For those who bought razer stuff for first time, this item is able to  be registered for warranty. 
And this item is what the 1st picture look like, not the second one (without the 2 sensitivity buttons)

I have previously used deathadder and still love the design and the two side buttons on the side. This Deathadder ELITE has a different texture on it, it has a good egonomics to it and the feel is more premium.

The product arrived quickly but the packaging for the box is kinda crappy, a thin paper wrapping around the box, offering almost no protection to the box which i got a few dents here and there. But the mouse in the box is fine,  so unless you wanna keep the box for display or whatnot, you mind want to reconsider. 

For the mouse itself, it is great! I have been using the Razer deathadder for 8 yrs already. The 3.5G ver, the 4G version and now this 5G version. And out of all of them, I like this current edition the most. The dpi adjustor below the mousewheel is a nice addition from the 4G edition of deathadder. The rubber grips on both sides of the mouse are a great feel as it came with the 4G edition too.

Overall it's a pretty damn good mouse but my experience with Razer hasn't been too great because they usually start to have problems right after the warranty is over which is about 2yrs.

The discontinued Imperator was a favorite amongst many users, and for someone like me who had no direct replacement, this was a prime choice. Ergonomics are even better than the Imperator, with a slightly higher arch, with a sharper taper to the right. To be clear, this is NOT an ambidextrous mouse. This Deathadder Elite Chroma has an updated grip with generous amounts of rubber on the thumb side and the pinky/ring finger end to ensure a firm clasp with minimal effort and strain. Long duration of use is perfect, with little to no fatigue. Again, up to personal preference on your grip style. Tested with Battlefield and COD, I dare say it works better = smoother and accurate. Polling rate at adjustable 125-1000hz with DPI setting that can go way too high for anyone's practical use (16000dpi).

Has 2 customizable buttons on the thumb area which I have assigned to Volume Up and Down. Sadly I can't seem to assign the 'Back' and 'Forward' default browsing functions to those buttons like how it was on my previous Imperator (which did help with productivity - again personal preference here). On top the extra two buttons are for Sensitivity Control, which you can assign a few stages of DPI settings through the Razer Synapse application.

Chroma function has numerous cycle patterns ranging from default 16M colors, to 'Breathing' between 2 colors, 'On Click' with a customizable fadeout, and static, or off. Overall, quality product, hope it lasts 7 of more years like my previous imperator.

Deathadder has always been known for its ergonomic design. Your hand will still feel comfy after prolong hours of gaming. Its on-the-fly dpi change is an excellent feature for gamers to switch between casual and gaming mode in this elite version. With its upgraded range of DPI which can go up to 16,000, its pretty sick. Otherwise, in general, it is similar to previous versions of deathadders.  Registered my product for warranty, thus its a genuine product.

product_name: Creative Sound Blaster Play! 3 - USB DAC AMP & External Sound Card
\u00e7omments:
Comparison I/O equipment:
- Native Instruments Komplete Audio 6
- MSI B250I Gaming Pro AC
- Meridian Explorer DAC

Headphones used to test:
- Sennheiser HD650
- Shure SRH840
- Koss PortaPros

Microphones tested:
- Antlion Modmic 5

Bought this as the mic input on my motherboard was too noisy and not sensitive enough for a Modmic. No setup required. Mic input has plenty of gain and a low noise floor, though of course not as low as entry-level studio equipment e.g. Komplete Audio 6 which costs several times more. 

Headphone output was decently average, not too different from my motherboard (MSI B250I Gaming). Will drive most regular headphones OK, but noise floor on headphone out is higher than I would like (see SNR spec of 93db). At the levels required to drive less sensitive headphones (e.g. Sennheiser HD650 at 300 ohms), the midrange gets grainy/shouty and it loses refinement, but on more sensitive cans like the Shure SRH840 it sounds decent, and with Koss PortaPros it sounds great.

TBH you should just get this if you have no intention of getting into audiophile type stuff. Ignore the 24/96 spec because you're not likely to use it (most consumer audio files output at 16/44.1), it's just a number for marketing at this price point. 

Otherwise it's a cheap and cheerful piece of kit that mostly does what it says on the tin, is good value for money, and is perfect if you just need to get around noisy or low output/input onboard sound.

Before this purchase, I had bought many brand-less sound cards that all sounded god awful with earphones. This has been the only sound card that has worked perfectly with earphones.

It is pocket-sized and functions as plug-n-play, it also offers a downloadable equaliser/surround sound software from Creative website. Definitely recommend this for anyone who has issues with their laptop sound card like me or simply wants an upgrade in sound output.

Excellent product by Creative! Tested on pc/laptop & ps4 just bring my older headsets back to life! Love it that is a small USB sound device that support 24bit 96kHz studio grade! Recommend totally! Big Thumbs UP up UP!!!
I realized my current sound card is better than SBP3 after using it for awhile -_-

GIGABYTE ULTRA DURABLE 4 PLUSGIGABYTE Ultra Durable 4 Plus debuts on GIGABYTE 8 Series motherboards, with a range of features and component choices that provide record-breaking performance, cool and efficient operation, and an extended motherboard lifespan. GIGABYTE uses All Solid Caps (Capacitors) and Low RDS(on) MOSFETs, which are rated to work at higher temperatures to provide a longer lifespan. GIGABYTE motherboards feature GIGABYTE DualBIOS, an exclusive technology from GIGABYTE that protects arguably one of your PC's most crucial components, the BIOS. GIGABYTE DualBIOS means that your motherboard has both a 'Main BIOS' and a 'Backup BIOS', making users protected from BIOS failure due to virus attack, hardware malfunction, improper OC settings, or power failure during the update process.

HIGH ESD PROTECTION FOR USB AND LAN (USB 3.0 ONLY)GIGABYTE 8 Series motherboards raise the bar in terms of protecting your system, providing advanced electrostatic discharge (ESD) protection for both your Ethernet LAN and USB ports, both common sources of ESD-related failures. Each LAN and USB port is paired with a dedicated protection filter that can withstand high electrostatic discharges, protecting your system from common electrical surges, and even direct lighting strikes.

ONE FUSE PER USB PORT (USB 3.0 ONLY)On GIGABYTE 8 Series motherboards each USB port has its own dedicated power fuse that prevents unwanted USB port failure, helping to safe guard your important data during transfer.

ON/OFF CHARGE TECHNOLOGYGIGABYTE On/Off Charge technology allows you to charge your iPhone, iPad and iPod Touch regardless of whether your PC is on, in standby mode or even off. A derivative of GIGABYTE's highly acclaimed 3x USB Power feature, On/Off Charge enables devices to draw more current from GIGABYTE motherboard USB ports than standard USB ports allow, so that charging from your PC can be as fast as with a charger. (*Due to certain mobile phone limitations, users may need to connect the mobile phone to their PC before the PC enters S4/S5 mode to enable a quick charge from non On/Off Charge USB ports. Charging results may vary by model. *Whether to support 3X USB power design, it may vary by models. )

LAN OPTIMIZER - INTELLIGENT OPTIMIZATION NETWORK MANAGEMENT TOOLGIGABYTE LAN Optimizer is designed to allow the user to manage different types of network traffic so that data streams such as HD media, web browsing, or online gaming can be prioritized, taking precedence over large data downloads that tend to strangle overall network bandwidth.

GIGABYTE APP CENTERGIGABYTE App Center gives you easy access to wealth of GIGABYTE apps that help you get the most from your GIGABYTE motherboard. Using a simple, unified user interface, GIGABYTE App Center allows you to launch all GIGABYTE apps installed on your system.

\u00e7omments:
Usually you wouldn't consider buying laptop from online stores, that's what I thought until I saw this gen-8 processor laptop (i5-8250U is fast).

I needed a portable one for work, so this 1.6kg ultrabook fits the bill (despite its lack of gpu). The storage space is actually 200GB after you account for system files etc, but it's plenty fast because its SSD. The screen is not that good though, under bright light the quality is terrible. Just watch youtube video of this laptop and you will see what I mean. The battery, on the other hand, doesn't last as long as 10 hours as stated in the specs. It can last a good 6-8 hours depending on what you do with it. (Got to wait and see how fast it drains)

I got an automated whatsapp message telling me that my parcel will be delivered today. And if I'm not around, I can provide verification code to the ninja when he calls to leave the parcel somewhere safe. (Not sure how it works cos 1) Ninja didn't call and 2) I was at home)

It came in a black plastic wrap with scotch tape that says, "Fragile handle with care." Inside is a box covered with bubble wrap - in the box contains the notebook, charger and a acer carrybag. Props to Ninja Van for their delicate handling of the laptop. All in all, I will recommend this if you need a portable, light, fast loading ultrabook. If you need it for gaming, this is not the one for you.

The printer is small and compact. Setup is simple: remove the printer from the box, slot in the toner, connect the power, press the WPS button on my router and the wifi button on the printer for auto connection and voila the printer is connected to my home wifi network. 

Tested a sample print out and the output looks ok. Overall quite happy with the purchase.

Very efficient and economical printer with a very decent price. However, I had a hard time configuring it for network print because the WPS function was unable to work (unable to retrieve IP address).

Product delivered promptly and working well. Supplier also gave me a can of photcopy cleaner!
Great service.
The printer came earlier than the expected date. The product was easy to set up and bam I was on my way.

Great value for money. Overall the printer is pretty compact. The wireless function is easy to set up and use, pairs easily with my Macbook Air. Just turn on the printer and you can immediately print wirelessly.

I purchased the white/rose gold version and so far I've been thoroughly impressed by the quality. Been using them everyday for two solid weeks now and so far it has never failed me. I'm no audiophile but I can't deny that the sound quality is great. You get a very punchy bass and clear vocals. Also, three additional different sized eartips are included to ensure that the earbuds fit well. A great purchase for anyone who (like me) are looking for a good quality and reasonably priced pair of earphones.

The build and material used are amazing for something priced like this. The metal feels solid and the wiring is good. 

However there is a downside for iOS users that the product does not describe until you open the packaging. That is iOS users are not able to use the control to increase and decrease the volume, only start, stop and skip songs.

Overall this is not a deal breaker for me because I am still able to use the mic and if I want to change the volume I can just do it on my phone, it's more important for me that you are able to skip songs using the controls.
